  "texts": [
    "This is well-known, and it follows from rigidity of homogeneous gradient solitons [PW09].",
    "Indeed, any homogeneous gradient soliton is isometric to (a quotient of) R k × E n-k, where E is Einstein and R k flat.",
    "In particular, its Ricci curvature is semi-definite, and this contradicts a result of Milnor [Mil76].",
    "□ Remark 6.4.",
    "Proposition 6.3 also shows that, even in the abelian case, many of the solitons we constructed are of non-gradient type."
  ],
